**TL;DR: Everything You Need to Know About Cushion Cut Diamonds**

A cushion cut diamond is a square or rectangular brilliant-cut diamond with rounded corners and curved sides — shaped like a pillow, which is exactly where the name comes from.

It is the third most popular engagement ring shape in 2026, sitting behind round brilliant and oval, and the most historically significant — until the early 20th century, the cushion cut was the dominant diamond shape globally, and the Hope Diamond — one of the most famous diamonds in the world — is a cushion cut.

**Live May 2026 price snapshot:**

-   1ct natural H-VS2 Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$1,770](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27404713?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.
-   1ct natural H-VVS2 Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$1,760](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27035330?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.
-   1ct lab-grown E-IF Ideal Cut GCAL: **[$1,590](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28341626?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.
-   2ct natural G-VS2 Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$10,470](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23940802?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.
-   2ct lab-grown D-IF Ideal Cut GIA starts at **[$9,740](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26984912?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**.

**The one thing every buyer must know before reading further:** There are two fundamentally different cushion cut styles — "Chunky" (standard) and "Crushed Ice" (modified brilliant) — that look completely different in real life despite sharing the same GIA shape description.

Buying a cushion cut without understanding this distinction is the most common and most expensive mistake in cushion cut shopping. This guide resolves it completely.

**Buy a cushion cut if:**

-   You want a romantic, vintage-inspired aesthetic with modern brilliance
-   Budget efficiency matters — cushions cost 20–35% less than round brilliants at equal quality
-   You want the shape most forgiving of inclusions among all square/rectangular shapes
-   You want the shape best suited to fancy color diamonds

**Do not buy a cushion cut if:**

-   You want maximum apparent size per carat — oval appears larger
-   You want a shape with a standardized GIA cut grade — GIA does not grade cushion cut quality
-   You want sharp, geometric, modern lines — princess or radiant delivers this better

